28:13.525 --> 28:14.726 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
its battles.

28:14.760 --> 28:16.562 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Hari Sreenivasan has our
conversation.

28:16.595 --> 28:21.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: A new report
published by
the Combating Terrorism Center
at West Point

28:21.066 --> 28:26.104 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
chronicles the increasing use of
children
as fighters for the so-called
Islamic State.

28:26.138 --> 28:29.675 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The report's authors, based at
Georgia State
University in Atlanta,
documented the Islamic

28:29.708 --> 28:35.914 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
State's own propaganda, which
praises deceased
young fighters as martyrs. It
shows how the

28:35.948 --> 28:41.920 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
group uses children and youth in
suicide operations.
They found three times as many
suicide attacks

28:41.954 --> 28:45.657 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
involving young people in
January of this
year than last year.

28:45.691 --> 28:50.062 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For more on the study's findings
and what
they mean, we're joined by one
of the report's

28:50.095 --> 28:51.863 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
authors, professor Mia Bloom.

28:51.897 --> 28:56.768 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Problem Bloom, unfortunately,
child soldiers
aren't anything new. So, how is
ISIS using

28:56.802 --> 28:58.437 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
them differently?

28:58.470 --> 29:02.574 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MIA BLOOM, Georgia State
University: So, we
started our study with a
baseline looking

29:02.608 --> 29:06.511 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
at the literature on child
soldiers, looking
at biographies and
autobiographies of people

29:06.545 --> 29:11.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who had been child soldiers, in
order to get
a sense of what we thought we
might expect.

29:11.850 --> 29:16.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so we expected that children
would be
used when they ran out of adults
or when they

29:16.121 --> 29:20.726 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
couldn't find adults, or that
children would
be used against civilian
targets. And we didn't

29:20.759 --> 29:26.398 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
find either of those. Instead,
what we found
was that children in ISIS are
used alongside

29:26.431 --> 29:31.970 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the adults, not instead, and, in
fact, only
3 percent of the time were
children used against

29:32.004 --> 29:37.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
civilian targets; 61 percent of
the time,
they were going after what we
would call hard

29:37.109 --> 29:40.545 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
targets, military, police,
militias and the
army.

29:40.579 --> 29:43.048 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: So they're
doing just what
the grownups do.

29:43.081 --> 29:47.619 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIA BLOOM: They're doing exactly
what the
grownups do, and, in fact, we
found considerably

29:47.653 --> 29:50.389 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
more suicide bombers than anyone
expected.

29:50.422 --> 29:55.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And you said
-- you actually
break it down; 39 percent are
driving basically

29:55.761 --> 29:57.562 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
car bombs?

29:57.596 --> 30:02.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIA BLOOM: Thirty-nine percent
were car bombs.
These were vehicle-borne
improvised explosive

30:02.501 --> 30:05.570 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
device, so it's a VBIED.

30:05.604 --> 30:09.741 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But many of the children were
also wearing
what we would call a suicide
belt, which is

30:09.775 --> 30:16.314 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
an individual IED that is
attached to them,
so they were part of these
marauding raids,

30:16.348 --> 30:21.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
these inghimasi, so they would
go into the
target, shoot and then blow up
the IED or

30:21.920 --> 30:24.423 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the suicide belt at the end of
the operation.

30:24.456 --> 30:29.428 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Now, it used
to be that
groups would recruit in secret,
that they

30:29.461 --> 30:33.198 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
knew that there was going to be
societal backlash.
This is the opposite.

30:33.231 --> 30:37.202 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You're saying in your report
that ISIS brags
about the fact that they're
recruiting young

30:37.235 --> 30:39.004 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
kids.

30:39.037 --> 30:42.174 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIA BLOOM: Not only is ISIS
boasting that
they're using these children,
but they're

30:42.207 --> 30:45.610 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
using the children also in a way
to humiliate
the men.

30:45.644 --> 30:51.917 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What we didn't put into report,
but will be
exploring further, is that ISIS
is using the

30:51.950 --> 30:57.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
children, for example, in the
prison to determines
who lives and dies. They're also
using the

30:57.255 --> 31:02.294 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
children to actually carry out
the execution,
and so they're empowering the
children, and

31:02.327 --> 31:05.897 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
by doing so, disempowering the
men.

31:05.931 --> 31:10.102 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And this is a way in which they
are recruiting
the children to basically feel
like you will

31:10.135 --> 31:15.240 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be more than what you are. You
won't be a
child in a society where you're
lesser than,

31:15.273 --> 31:19.444 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but you will be powerful, you
will be a cub
and then eventually a lion.

31:19.478 --> 31:25.684 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: As you watched
through all
of these images and videos, you
actually point

31:25.717 --> 31:30.388 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
out that almost half these
children have smiles
on their faces, at least in the
propaganda

31:30.422 --> 31:32.724 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that comes out after. Explain
that.

31:32.758 --> 31:36.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIA BLOOM: Well, one of the
things that we
tried to do is, we're trying to
get a sense

31:36.661 --> 31:41.299 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
